just_use loose_card_play.go

# label: INTRICATE
# role: encodes domain knowledge

"Move one board card to a new home, then play a hand card on the resulting
board." The most computationally expensive trick — quadruple-nested loop
over (src stack, src card, dest stack, stranded hand card) with a
simulateMove in the inner check.

**Pre-filter:** only hand cards that CAN'T already direct-play are
"stranded" and worth the combinatorial search. Cards that extend something
already will be picked up by direct_play; this trick rescues cards that
have no home.

peelIntoResidual is a narrower variant of extractCard that for middle-of-
run splits returns only the LEFT half — the right half wouldn't accept
the hand card in a loose-move context, so we don't bother materializing it.
